German Chancellor Angela Merkel on Wednesday called Turkey&#8217;s latest arrests of opposition newspaper journalists &#8220;highly alarming&#8221; and said they would impact Ankara&#8217;s EU membership negotiations.&#8220;For me and the entire government, it is highly alarming that freedom of the press and speech are being further restricted,&#8221; she said after Turkey detained at least a dozen journalists and executives of Cumhuriyet daily.-AFP